\proof[size="18pt"]{October 15th, 1953 and October 17th, 1981–both were good days for me! Mobile +254 376 958 517, Home +1 972 296-6145 ~Good-bye, friend Cal, Saturday, 4 Aug 2018 at 14:28. Psalm 116:15~ Nearly 260 yrs ago Capt Cook set sail in 1768 (on Aug 24th, in fact) once again, dialing +5 831 945 5264 at 22:40. He reached -16.498019° S, -151.759428° W before landing. Etwa 50% haben 37° im £50 und ¥20 sind $30 und €60 den §235 sowie #35 Toff 47 comal Seite 3f und 12/f_f . Der §45a in den 20ern. I'm reading 1 Samuel 6:1-19, learning more about David. In 1 Chronicles 11 we hear about the 30 and then the 3; in chapter 15 we learn of the 120 sons of Kohath, the 220 sons of Merari, the sons of Gershom, numbering 130, the 200 sons of Elizaphan, Hebron's 80 sons, and the 112 sons of Uzziel. March 4th, 2017, at 5 o'clock in the afternoon. June 3rd, 2013, at 4:30ish, if I remember correctly.}

